caption: It was not busy but somehow they managed to forget our order of jambalaya. It was bland. No spice. I paid an additional $4 for additional shrimp and only receive four tiny shrimp.
The oysters were good but the service was AWFUL! Waited 45 minutes for 6 oysters and watched others who ordered after us get food before us.

Bland food, needed salt...in New Orleans. Disjointed customer service. An overpriced tourist trap, mediocre at its best. There’s better food at the market, certainly all across town, and if you’re at the market — walking distance away from where you are. You deserve a better NOLA experience.
Really good don’t see why a lot of people didn’t like the food it was great in my opinion.

Terrible experience.  Waited for 25 minutes for a small boil of seafood gumbo...that tasted like ocean water and canned shrimp.  It was disgusting and so hot burnt my mouth. When I tried to return it...the father and son owner said they would call security...we threw it away....and left $9 poorer.  DONT EAT HERE...trust me there are so many other amazing places.

SAVE YOUR MONEY the best tasting item there was the bottled water....Father and son run like a poorly run food truck .. Ordered couple of seafood Gumbos....tasted like metal as if it came out a tin can.....DOESN'T REPRESENT NEW ORLEANS FOOD WHAT-SO-EVER.......WOULD NOT EVER RETURN FOR FOOD PURCHASE ....MAYBE IF I NEEDED ANOTHER. BOTTLED WATER..... -1 rating

During our trip to the French Quarter we visited a lot of the more upscale restaurants of the area...Places we had researched ahead of time...But let me tell you, Nawlins had the BEST food BY FAR, of our entire trip!!  One day my two daughters and I were wandering the artist booths of The French Market, and decided we were hungry. We saw Nawlins and decided to give them a try. We ordered seafood gumbo, and the BBQ shrimp. Those shrimp were the highlight of our entire trip! We ended up walking to the market the next day to have another plate of those delicious shrimp before we had to catch our plane home. The man who runs it is great. Very friendly service. Its a family run place, that is 4 generations strong. Make sure to stop in and see them when you visit New Orleans!
Food was really good and the service was awesome! Highly recommend to anyone in the French market area.
This was the best meal I found while in New Orleans.
Fun market to pick up gifts to take back home.
$18 for a small poboy with stale bread
Great food! There was a wait, but it was worth ut!

The crawfish poboy was good, but not worth the $18 and 48 minutes I waited for it on a slow day. The girl in line next to me had been there over an hour still waiting on her jambalaya which was on the "quick" menu.

Food was really good, but really spicey hot. Employee was walking around with his pants almost down to his knees with his entire butt sticking out under his underwear. Another employee blew his nose in a tissue, and I didn't see him wash his hands before handling food.

If this was the only place in the French Market, Id never return To New Orleans. The service was beyond slow. They forgot my order, and what should have been 10 mins took almost half an hr. And when the food did arrive. it was disgustingly salty.
Amazing customer service! Definitely worth a visit!

The wait and Food were both horrific! Other family members were already done eating their lunch by the time my daughters simple rice plate came out…It tasted terrible and we had to throw it out! I rarely ever rate establishments, but they were so rude to our family, we have never been treated like this anywhere in the world that we have traveled. Pick other places to eat as this place can’t even be called a restaurant.

This place is horrible. Food seems like it’s old . I waited 45minutes for a shrimp poboy and jambalaya that was hard like it had been in the microwave to long. I also saw pretty decent size Rats running around in the area that later went into there business. I asked for a refund and they denied me after waiting 45mins . Food is over priced for little portions. This was a horrible experience.DO NOT EAT HERE

We waited over 40 minutes for food. Finally just asked for our money back. THEN they decoy to make the food. Refused to give money back. Ordered greens over rice. Got a TINY half scoop of rice with some soupy veggie mix. Do NOT eat at this awful place!!!!!!!
I don’t ever review places.  But this is by far the most unorganized restaurant I’ve ever been too.  Over an hour wait for just ok food.  I can getter better points in minutes in Texas.
We waited 45 minutes for mediocre crawfish etouffee. Sandwiches were better but not worth the wait.
Terrible service and long wait time.

Service was quick but the food was a waste of money. I ordered the alligator bites; 5 came on the It is a breaded hushpuppy and if you look at the last pic in my review that was the alligator inside. The barbeque sauce made it taste better. The potatoes were spicy and mushy. So to say the least I haven't had decent alligator on this trip.

The service is terrible. The wait time is over 30 United for a quick bite spot on the French market. The server was nasty when I inquired about my food and wishing to cancel due to the long wait time. They have a no cancellation policy. Don’t go and order if you can’t wait. If you see a crowd there walk away unless you have plenty of patience waiting
Overpriced

Edited - Two stars instead of one because I was able to eat the food.  Service was slow and there wasn’t a line. Our food came out in three different stages over a 30 minute period. Food was overpriced, but tasted fine. I expected much more from a place boasting “BEST FOOD IN New Orleans.”

Super unorganized, mediocre food quality and overpriced. There are so many good places in New Orleans, avoid this place and go somewhere else.  We ordered alligator bites and waited for over 20mins...until we realized the server had put them on the counter on the other side (around the corner) without telling us, so we had to eat them cold. Another customer ordered some food and the server gave this order to the wrong customer, the woman at the counter then made him chase this customer down (she was sitting down at a table to eat already), took the order back and gave the opened bag to the original customer. The kitchen personnel were also constantly on their phones and then preparing food without washing their hands after touching their phones...NO GLOVES either
It's a bit pricey, so I ordered something small. I ended up getting the alligator on a stick. It was flavorful and juicy. It was worth the $8.

Incredible waste of time and money.   I've had better beans and rice out of a box, and the portion size was actually laughable.  The employee/manager was rude and dismissive.   DO NOT waste your New Orleans experience on this .
the food was yummy but we waited 45 minutes till our (small) dish was ready
Honestly go somewhere else. Over priced, very small portions, with no flavor. Honestly I’ve had better food in county.
My $5 beer filled me up more than the $30 platter here. Look elsewhere if you need an actual meal.
Save your time and money
I got over priced Shrimp po boy here which tasted just ok. Go elsewhere!

I've never written a review on here before but I just had to for this place, it was that bad! WAY overpriced for what you get. I ordered the po boy and the bread was stale, and there was hardly any crawfish in it! I thought for a $19 sandwich it would be stuffed with crawfish and fixings, but there was hardly anything there, instead of a po boy it was like I had bread with a bit of something else in it, not a sandwich at all. My mom's order didn't even come out, she had to go up to the counter to ask about it because they had forgotten it. Terrible food, terrible service. DO NOT GO THERE.
This place charged me $25 for a Lobster Po-Boy and medium drink. It was imitation lobster, and the sandwich was mostly bread. Disappointed in the food and service was mediocre.

It's funny how all of the local guides reviews are the only 5 star reviews that this restaurant receives.  I know them to be paid for reviews. There's a reason for that, and that's because the food is sub-par, overpriced and they take forever to serve. I'm a local and there are much better places to go for a bite that are much less "tourist-trappy".

(Translated by Google) $ 25 for 2 burgers of - supposedly - alligator, but that tasted like pure refused oil.  (Original) 25$ por 2 hamburguesas de -supuestamente- alligator, pero que me supieron a puro aceite rehusado.
I ordered the Turkey Po-boy, the bread was old , it feel apart.
Very overpriced with a long wait, not even worth the wait or cost whatsoever. Keep walking.
Food was amazing. Service from the two ladies that were taking orders were a little uninviting and rude.

What happened?! This used to be the place for gator bites when we lived here several years ago. Now they serve this mess for 12$ and a 30min wait! Oh but complain about the wait because the receipt has a clause, "During holidays and festivals you may expect 45-1hour wait." They offered to remake it (not refund it), but I didn't have time to wait another 30mins for something that was supposed to be a quick fried snack to eat on the go.

Ordered bbq shrimp and seafood gumbo, both tasted horrid and I wish we had eaten somewhere else. Took 20mins to arrive and accompanying bread was stale, we asked for fresh bread and they gave us burger bun as an alternative as that’s all they head. Even after complaining we didn’t really get any apologi

I ordered the gumbo and my bf ordered the chicken and shrimp pasta. 15 minutes after we ordered they told us they ran out of chicken and could provide extra shrimp.  The pasta was very bland and it only included a few pieces of shrimp. We expressed our dissatisfaction and the woman said I could not get a refund or could not swap it out for something different on the menu. We ended up throwing away the food and wasting $18. They opened the door to the kitchen and we could see the cook making food for other customers with no gloves on. The woman also told us the food was made fresh but then I saw the cook throw someone's meal in the microwave before serving it. Save your money.

The food is alright. We're a little disappointed that the food was bland. The seafood platter had a lot of seasoning on top of the fish but not inside the fish. The burger was bland. The shrimp boudin also needs a little more seasoning, the shrimp is a little rubbery. I guess you can say we expected the creole food to have a little more seasoning in general. We saw the cook take out the shrimp boudin pit it in a microwave,  take it out, put a stick in it and wrapped it in foil and gave it to a customer. Do not order any of the pastas. The person taking our order was super nice.
Clean, courteous, good selection, good customer service.
Expensive and very low quality. Gumbo was decent but poboys were appealing, very salty, small portioned, and bad tasted.

The flavor was there, though when you go in hungry, do NOT order the Crawfish Etoufee’! The Po’boy is a much better deal. I pointed out that there were only six crawfish in the dish with more rice and bread than stew and was told that it was the normal portion. The Po’boy was much better fitted to the location and had more than twice the crawfish load as the etoufee’ for several dollars less. I also brought my own cup and asked for some water from the tap and was told I could get ice, but they couldn’t serve me water. Ridiculous! The service wasn’t great either, though it didn’t help that one of the employees had called in sick. Ok to go to for a bite to eat, but not as highly recommended as I would have hoped.
So many better options within feet of this place. Overpriced and bland, and the “gator bites” were definitely not gator.

If I could make the review less than 1 star I would. Firstly, there is no coordination with staff. My husband and I ordered a Cajun Shrimp Pasta and a Nawlins Burger, we waited for service for literally 45 mins. When we got it, it was literally a burger that could have been made on a hotplate in 10 mins. The pasta that I was told was being made fresh to order was cold and broken as if it was a pasta that was reheated. Finally I asked for a refund, I didn't demand one like another customer did in the same hr timeframe, but we were both told that we would not be refunded because the receipt states that on HOLIDAYS and PARADE DAYS that wait could be anywhere from a 45-1hr wait, it wasn't a holiday or parade day but the dude in the back insisted that that also applies to when they have a number of excess customers, also the receipt does actually state no refunds so please please please, I advise you to be careful if choosing this place to eat at because I'm almost positive you will not be satisfied.  Oh P.S. the amount spent on the meal was $45 something. You tell me if that was worth the food. But I will state that their fruit lemonades are good. I guess that's worth the one star.
DO NOT GO TO THIS PLACE! Po-BOY was overpriced and was worth 5$. Then they just charged me a 5$ extra tip on my card which I didn't permited. Stay away!
Best gumbo in the city of New Orleans! Bread pudding is to die for! Food is delicious, staff is great & they have spices available!
The seafood platter is outstanding let alone the service was spectacular — highly recommended!! 5 stars.

The catfish poboy,  my husband received was horrible. The fish looked good but the bread was as hard as a crouton. It was pretty impossible to eat the bread. The only reason I can give this establishment a 2 is because of the potatoes and the voodoo burger I received was okay. Otherwise this establishment would have received a 1.
Food is delicious. Bit pricey for the portion you get. Good for a light lunch. Expect to wait.
Worst experience in New Orleans. Po Boy and dirty rice not at all what I expected. Manager was rude as hell. Girl was on her phone cursing.. Please save your money and DO NOT GO. PERIOD.

This is by far the worst stand in the French Market! We ordered a lobster Po Boy for $18 which turned out to be imitation lobster meat!!!! We approached them discreetly to return it, they took the plate from us then call the nastiest excuse for a manager, who refused to give us our money back or even offered anything else after taking an uneaten sandwich from us. When we refused to leave and started telling everyone that stopped by about our experience which in term cost them to lose a lot of business, he got on the phone to call the cops! When the police officer arrived he listened to us and try to reason with the jerk of a manager but he still wouldn’t bulge. And basically told us we needed to file a civil complaint. This place is trash and the so called manager is a disgrace. I hope the owner reads this review and thinks strongly about who he has working for him.
Food was good but over priced for the amount you are given.
I don't know why the other reviews say that the food was cold! It's darn hot and delicious. Got some gator bites and worth every penny.
Red beans and rice is delicious

This place is a joke. The manager is a little boy who doesn’t do anything but do drugs. The food is the most disgusting food I have ever seen. I did not even eat my meal. I saw the “manager” drop my food in the garbage because he was upset that I told him the food was horrible and cold . He picked it up again took and stored it for a another customer. Please please someone call the health inspector on this disgusting establishment. Please beware and safe. Do not order anything from this dirty restaurant.
Great place to try different foods!
Waiting 50 minutes still no food...NOT A QUICK BITE. NEVER GOT OUR FOOD AFTER AN HOUR
AMAZING!
Great place for tourists to eat and try their first bowl of authentic Creole gumbo. This place has a vegetarian menu as an option also.

Was walking through the market when I saw a plethora of spices, and picked up a few because I figure, you can never have too many on hand in the kitchen. The young man stocking the shelves was helpful and polite. The lady behind the counter (cashier) was funny as hell, personable, and good humored. I didn't try any food, as I had breakfast first before going to the market and wasn't hungry, so I can't speak on that. The customer service was good, so I've got zero complaints.

Stopped for a quick bite as we passed through the market. Perfect for what we were looking for and the gator on a stick was tasty and so was the creole bread pudding! The gator sausage had a little spice to it and had a similar taste to fried bologna for those who aren't sure of the flavor.

Had the red beans and rice not very flavorful but I guess it will do if your hungry not a spot to go if your Seeking good food on a budget stick to my other top choices if you're looking for a palette pleasing
The flavour of the Gumbo and Jambalaya was second to none and the service was to a high standard! I will dream of these flavors when I leave New Orleans!
Crazy. Waited 45 min. for the food. They never say sorry. The food was expensive and small amount of food. Never go there.
Worst service. Takes more than an hour to serve the food and it’s cold.
I think Zatarain's box mix is better.

It was a horrible experience.  It took 45 minutes to get the jambalaya that I ordered and it was cold.  The addes $3.99 shrimp were complete mush on top of the jambalaya and it wasnt peeled.  They left shells on it.  It tasted like they were months old.

Worst gumbo I have ever tried “authentic gumbo “ I don’t think so it was cold and tasted spoiled as well. I don’t know about you but cold seafood gumbo sound like I would have been up sick all night if I ate it. when I mentioned it to the owner he took my gumbo and didn’t give me a refund or another dish comparable so really they stolen my money. I guess if they can’t refund 10 dollars life must be hard at the n’awlins . I don’t recommend eating Here try mothers nature’s cupboard

If I could I would give this place a 0 but unfortunately Google don't allow you to do that my mother and I stopped in here to have some gumbo authentic gumbo from New Orleans it was not what we were served it was rotten gumbo and when we went back to get a refund and actually just switch it out for some gators stick that was cheaper we got told NO they do nothing like that they took the bowl of gumbo and didn't refund my mother her money or compromise with her the guy continue to argue with us I would not recommend this place to anyone it would be a wast of money we also got a plate of jambalaya that was a plate of mushy rice not cool

My family and I was dining for an early lunch. The order processors were very confused and there was much order to the process. We still ordered for three adults and with tip our bill was around 58 bucks. I was surprised to find out that a refill of coke was 1.50 each.  The food was okay but not on the must stop or come back to list.

The food was alright, at best. But the prices were way overinflated for the quality of the food. The tamales were very dry and cold. My chief complaint is they refused to refill my Coke. I spent almost a hundred dollars at this establishment and for them not to refill a Coke was pretty pathetic. And yes this was a fountain drink. I have never been to a restaurant that did not refill Fountain drinks. I cannot recommend this place in good conscience.
Gators on stick can use more seasoning but still tasty nevertheless (it’s my first time having gator, kinda like pork but different), bread pudding with rum sauce is really nice
Terrible! No taste, bad quality food, dirty. Outrageously expensive, U$ 24 for a PO Boy Shrimp and 6 sips of Coke

Overpriced items and will not let you return the items. Was mislead that they would ship my items and after I made the purchase they said it was only for items that I ordered later. DO NOT GO HERE!!!! They are nothing but shiesters! Zero stars if I could

If I could give zero stars I would. The food was absolutely terrible. We tried to have the jumbalaya but “they were out” and only told us after we had been waiting for 20 minutes. So we had the shrimp and grits and shrimp creole and they were almost exactly the same and both were gross, soupy, sour piles of something that might have resembled food a long, long time ago. The prices are astronomical for the portion size and quality. You’d be better off at a McDonalds. Actually, you’d be better off anywhere. The best possible outcome of this meal is explosive diarrhea; maybe I might lose weight and make this meal worth the $25 paid.
A little bit tough to find with GPS.  Once we realized it was in the market it was worth the effort
Absolutely wonderful! and the Alligator Po Boy with Creole potatoes couldn't be more exceptional! They are open daily at 830am so hurry down and get your bums down here!

I give 5 stars!  Even though I waited 55 minutes for a crawfish budin, the flavor was worth every minute of that wait!    It's the French market I feel like Its to be expected! The dirty rice was to die for!!   FLAVOR FLAVOR FLAVOR!         The owner had such a good soul!  He took pride in his work!! Big sweetheart!  When my food was taking a while he went back and cooked it himself! And he even told us a little of the history behind nawlins!!  I will 100% be back!!

If google allowed you to give zero stars, I would. But unfortunately I’m forced to give the worst place to eat in Nola one star. The food took forever to come out, and in the end we were charged $30 for the most underwhelming, tasteless dish I have ever had. We got the seafood platter, and the rice was undercooked and runny, the crabs had no meat inside, the few pieces of shrimp that came with it was overly salted, and the fish tasted like absolutely nothing. I am never one to give staff a hard time, but after tasting the food, we brought it up to them the issues that we had and they simply just told us that this is just how they cooked their food and there was nothing wrong with it. A horrible experience that I would not recommend to anyone.

A good friend of mine from Miami Florida named Kevin Crowder from the rock band McFisty asked me and New Orleans native producer Dale Patrick Latino to do him a favor on my last visit to New Orleans. He needed a spice called Nawlins Cajun Spice that is only sold at your cool place. Funny thing he owns a spice company called Red River Spice Company. I highly recommend that spices well he has an assortment of them. Anyway... We thought we can find it anywhere else so we went to like three or four other places but nobody had it as we were pressed for time for studio session. Even with having the address to place it was kind of hard to find. Plus they didn't answer the phone when we were calling to find the address. But we finally found the place and the service was awesome and the spice is incredible. All well worth the trouble we went through to get this specific spice. Thank you - Oski Gonzalez of The Oski Foundation
Sandwich was cold and the buns on burger was cold. Saw a waitress drop forks on floor and then put back in container!.  Was not worth 30$....wish we would have seen these reviews before we came here!
Great place to eat at in the French Market my go too.

Wish I saw all these reviews before coming here. Way overpriced $25 for a pasta and Coke. Then they forgot my order and it took and hour to get. No acknowledgement or sorries for the error. Go to Oceana and get a better meal for the same price or less.

Horrible business management, Manager is very rude. We simply got a small drink and it didn’t taste good, he told us we couldn’t change it out and started to question us! He really needs to work on proper etiquette!!

Beware, you are not told, but a cold sandwich will take 45 min to 1 hour to get.  No signs tell you that, but it is printed on the receipt.  However, you cannot cancel once you receive the receipt. On top of that, it is not even good food and is expensive.  The staff are extremely rude, they will argue with you.  You will always be the one that is wrong. They will not refund you money or make any effort to check on it.  If they fail to give you anything, you have to prove it.  I was just glad I did not get sick.  Bottom line: Buyer Beware!!!
This was disgusting. The shrimp wasn’t cooked. The pasta tasted re heated. I wasted over 17 dollars
I'd prefer to give this place no stars at all. But, "what eve"... Overpriced tasteless food. Anywhere else is bet'r.
Great food

My order was overpriced, wrong, mostly cold, and I waited over 30 minutes.  After I noticed multiple orders being filled after I had ordered I asked when long, staff told me that the other orders were first...  Kinda hard to be first when my order was placed first.  Large fountain sodas are 6.00....  no refills and mostly ice.

I ordered a lobster po boy. For $15 you'd think it would include some actual lobster on it. It was one of the most disgusting things I've ever bitten. Entirely imitation meat. And then the when I went to return it the ladies continued to lie to my face that it's real and insult me saying I don't know what lobster is. I wish I had read reviews first because apparently no one likes it here. I have never returned food to a restaurant before in my life. I love food. Almost nothing tastes bad to me. But this was so nasty.

$45 for two Po boys, and two lemonades. imitation lobster meat that looked more like crab salad. Was disappointed because the menu looked tasty and service was not bad. Do yourself a favor and go to literally anywhere else in/around the market to eat.
Worst $23 poboy I've ever had. Extremely slow service and food wasn't even made right. Avoid this place.

Worst Food and Worst Service. I received a to go box full of roaches. When I threw the box the roaches spread everywhere all over my Cajun Pasta which was disgusting by the way. Lucky I received my refund. Don't eat here. Prices are very high for disgusting food.
HORRIBLE!!!!!We’ll never go back to this pleace,HORRIBLE Service,HORRIBLE food,HORRIBLE prices

Stay away prices are high the food sucked small portion had no flavor and they have roaches.  We asked for a to go box and it was brought full of roaches over 30 roaches fell out of the container we got our refund but no apology for the bad experience we had roaches fell on us
Worst Experience Ever Asked For To Go Boxes & When We Pulled Them Apart A Family Full Of Roaches Came From The Boxes So Nasty !!!! & They Didnt Even Apologize Or Anything 😡😡
Etouffee tasted like nothing but straight up tomato. Gator tamales were wrapped in paper and covered in the same terrible tomato sauce.
Horrible. Overpriced garbage. Soft shell crab sandwich was inedible. Frog legs were rubber and flavorless.
Expensive, small portions for the price, slow and poor service, food arrived cold, poor quality.

Slow and food made incorrectly. No apology. Request for refund was ingnored/denied and told would make food again. One item was still not correct. Won’t return. Don’t waste your money. Tourist trap for those that don’t know better.
Worst gumbo in NOLA. DONT DO IT!! It's soupy sewage with a crab claw.
Like others have mentioned, portions were externally small for the price. Plus, we had to wait for almost 30 minutes for just one plate. It wasn’t even that busy. Not recommended!
So bad service and bad food. Different flavor and the attention is so bad. The people is patanes y groceros!! Badddddddd!!!!

I asked the lady taking orders if I can get extra bacon she said yes so after spending $13.95 for the Voodoo Burger I didn't get any bacon! I complained and she argued with me saying that's what I ordered so I asked them what was the extra charge for?
Taste of N'awlins sampler deal is trash.  Server recommended it and never made eye contact afterwards.  She knew it was horrible.
Sitting here now... small portions and high price. Gator bites were raw and the gumbo looked like sewage. Skip this spot.

$16 for a alligator po boy and $4 for a medium sweet tea... Im going to disregard the price of the sweet tea....... If I took my leather belt and cut it to a foot long and placed it on the sandwich, it would have tasted better than what I got. I don't know how this place could serve such a disgusting meal and have the audacity to ask you "is everything is ok?"....... Keep on walking if you see this place. I'm a avid food lover and never write reviews, this is by far the most horrible food I've ever had in my life.

SAVE YOUR MONEY!!! Food was awful! The portions of the food were very small for the price. My oldest daughter and I both ordered a burger. The taste reminded me of a burger you get at a high school cafeteria. My friend and my son ordered Gator bites and they were completely uneable. Smalled horrible and tasted even worse. Asked for something else and the owner said no they dont do that there. To top everything off food was all cold. After we left we were still hunrgy and had to go get more food somewhere else. We will never be back!!!

SAVE YOUR MONEY AND WALK AWAY! Portions were incredibly small for how expensive everything was. Ordered gator bites expecting them to be fried gator bites. They were chunks of meat that was barely was barely like warm and smelled extremely fishy and tasted even more fishy than they smelled. Also came with creole potatoes that were hard and also cold. Attempted to take back up to exchange for for something else and they told us they couldn't do that but the could reheat the plate. Red beans and rice and burgers were not good either. Also waited over 30 minutes for a child's pancake. Another lady waited over 30 minutes for her food too and said she had to leave and asked for a refund and they told her that they didn't do refunds. 7 of us in our group ate there and the only edible thing was tiny andouille sausage chunk my husband got with his red beans and rice.

Went here because i seen this place on furious Pete. Wish I hadn't gone here.  Ordered the taste of new orleans and a large drink and paid $34.28. The serving was small , the food was bland and not tasty at all. I'm sure the only reason pete said it was delicious was because of the Hot Sauce on it. My family and i were the only one ordering at this place. Should have gone next door where the crowd was. They looked much happier and satisfied with their meal.
Way over priced, even for a tourist area. They served a very small amount of food for a very high price. Food was good, but soup was watered down.

in the French Market ----It was completely and utterly disgusting! We ordered two soft shell crab  Po' Boys. The crab STILL had the guts inside. It was a shell instead of crab meat pretty much.  Terrible service, No refund given , he offered goods instead of a refund. NO THANKS.   Walk past this place.
it's my grandsons best friend

My husband and I had the Creole Breakfast Bowl. The grits were incredibly soggy. I've never had grits that runny. The service was bad and disorganized. I would note that the tamales weren't bad, but if the place can't make a simple southern staple well then you should worry.

Complaint Details I purchased the Red Beans & Rice dish from World Famous N'awlins Cafe for $9.95 + tax for a total of $11.02. When I received the plate it barely had food in it (much less $$9.95 worth of food). I requested that they kindly put more food on the plate and the employee rejected to do so. They stated that it was the portion that they served for that dish. I then requested that they switch out the dish and they refused to do so. I then requested for a refund and they refused that also. The staff was belligerent and rude towards me and other patrons that were having their own set of issues. I had purchased that dish and was regretful because it was not worth the money especially because the intention of purchasing that dish was to give it to a homeless man. I felt terrible that I gave him such a small portion. I was extremely dissatisfied and the "manager" that came out to address my concerns (after begging to speak to a manager for half an hour) told me "what you get is what you get". Unbelievable! I will never return to this establishment and will not recommend it to anyone!
I can't speak to the rest of the reviews. I had a soft shell crab Po Boy for breakfast and it was TO DIE FOR. 💯👏👌

They had alligator on a stick! :)  It was a sausage, I was hoping for more of a "skewer", such as you'd see used for chicken, but that was just my expectation.  The staff were friendly but the wait for food was very long, even though there wasn't a line.  The sausage was delicious though and worth trying.  There's a small sitting area and a ton of spices for purchase.

Tried ordering their Cajun pasta - "no pasta" Tried ordering gator bites - said on sign they didn't have it, along with 5 other menu items they didn't have Saw a kids gator burger come out and looked like the blandest thing I've ever seen. Decided right there and then that if they didn't have anything and what they did have looked like that - not worth it.

The soft shell crab poboy was a total disgrace ... just some smashed crab that was still in the shell, and it was $15. The gumbo was quite soupy and just had a big piece of crab thrown in the middle. We asked for a partial refund and were told they dont give refunds. What a joke of an operation! I wouldnt send my worst enemy here.
Food was decent, but the workers and other guests sitting at the bar were great company!
40 minute wait and the food was terrible. Save your money and time by going somewhere else.

Horrible!!! They used way too much over cooked okra. Made the dish extremely slimy. I paid $14 for a bowl and simply thru away. I noticed two other customers not happy and trying to get their money back. Took about 20 mins to get my bowl of Creole gumbo. I would not recommend it to anyone.
Service is terrible waited almost an hour to get a burger and when I finally got it my burger was soggy. I don't recommend this place to anyone.
(Translated by Google) Nice market with a lot of tourists junk. Still worth it.  (Original) Schöner Markt mit viel Touristen-Ramsch. Lohnt trotzdem.
Cajun swamp burger was terrible, no flavor at all and pattie looks like it was boiled. It was served with sautéed creole potatoes which doesn't go with burgers very well. Overall waste of money.

Food was good but not really worth the wait.  Took forever to get our meal. The cashier walked away, talking on the phone to smoke while people waited in line to place an order. She didn't move until her cigarette  was finished. The people waiting ahead of us were told 15 minutes into us waiting that they didn't have some of the ingredients  to make their meal. Horrible, and slow service. Go else were for better service and food.
Slow staff. Not worth the wait. I mean come on. It's meat on a stick. I should not have  to wait for 30 minutes.

Like all places in the French Market, they run out of stuff later in the day. Loved their Okra Gumbo and Etoufee. They prepare it fresh (you can see the kitchen from the side seats) so depending what you order, it is not a fast food experience. They also sell tons of spices so while you wait you can check that out. Service is friendly. Try to come on weekends, Therese will be there and she is the best.

Ordered 2 items on March 24. April 19, I still had not received my items, or any communication. Emailed them on the 19th, their response was that they were out of one the items Id ordered-did I want something else? I asked them to cancel my order-im still waiting...
The owners R the best on the Nautical Mile. Fresh ingredients make great dishes!

I don't normally take the time to write reviews, but for the sake of other tourists I did this time.  I have been visiting New Orleans for years, it's almost like a second home for me. However, when ordering one of my favorite Cajun dishes (jambalaya) I was utterly disappointed. I will not go into detail, but I will say that this business definitely does not reflect the traditional quality and reputation of New Orleans food. I tried returning my meal, but both hostesses insisted that it was in fact the correct way of making the dish, which I found embarrassing on their part. Please do not waste $10 for under-cooked "traditional" jambalaya. New Orleans has much more to offer! :-)
Food was alright, service was terrible. The women behind the counter wouldn't acknowledge us or answer any of our questions.
Tourist food!! This whole area is no more than a tourist trap. Hit I-10 west then take West End Boulevard and head out to the lakefront restaurants. Several restaurants there that the locals eat at.

The cashier was not open at the spice shop on Lundi Gras, and we had to wait in a long long line with customers ordering meals. On Ash Wednesday, they were sold out of nearly everything at the cafe, and the waitress was not very nice even after waiting a long time for our take-out order which was first delivered on plates. Then, she tried to give it another customer who was complaining they had to check out of their hotel. When we finally did get our order, it was wrong and incomplete even after being sent back for correction multiple times. In addition, the portions are half and the price is twice other restaurants nearby. My husband does like the Voodoo Hot Sauce (HOTTEST EVER) we brought home.
If you don't eat here you're a fool.
This was the smell rolling through the french market that was so good.  Wife had the creole breakfast bowl that was sufficient for two, and I had the tilapia po boy.  Both were great.
I ate there twice it was delicious, the staff was great. If you go have the barbecue shrimp. That's what I had both times.
Nice place. I had the alligator burger.  Had a flavor that's kind of hard to describe.  Unusual but good.
The jambalaya was horrible, nasty and not edible, service was the worst, would not refund, stay away

This restaurant was apparently on the Food Network show "Mystery Diners." They cooperated in a show that is obviously staged, and most likely for illicit reasons. I will NEVER go to this restaurant after they showed the world how foolish they are by participating in this charade.
Poor quality, long wait, high prices, save your time and money, so many places to eat in French Market, select one of those!
The service is bad and the food is worse. Tamales were half that size of a breakfast sausage link.
They have some of the best Seafood Gumbo. Highly recommend.

I had a crab Po-boy and my husband had the barbecue shrimp.  The crab meat on the Po-boy was grossly over salted and practically inedible.  The broth for the barbecue shrimp was also very salty that my husband had to pick out the shrimp from the broth.   We were afraid we'd get high blood pressure for the salt overdose.    Try at your own risk.   I would definitely not recommend this place to eat. We told the servers that the food was too salty and she only apologized but did not offer to remedy the situation.  We will never eat here again.

Places with lines are usually good signs that a place is tasty. This place has a line because it takes them 40 minutes to make a mediocre shrimp po-boy sandwich. Not to mention it was $16. Avoid. It's New Orleans. Stick with a liquid lunch.
Alligator Poboy was great and the potatoes with it were incredible. Great seasoning so we bought some
Best food this trip by far. These folks are not afraid to spice it up.
